HEADWORD: Tupperware party
<hw>Tupperware party</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a social gathering at which
the host (or more typically hostess) entertains the guests, and provides
them with an opportunity to order Tupperware. This was used as an
effective sales strategy by the Tupperware manufacturer, and provided
income to the host(ess) from commissions on sales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tuque</ent>⟦br⟧
